OL,3,CBritain's 'saddest shopping centre':
OL,4,COne in three shops shut in some areas
OL,6,FOne diner told me: "I love spending my
OL,7,Ftime in Wigston. If there's one thing
OL,8,FI wouldn't move from Wigston for, it's
OL,9,Fthe town centre. It's very convenient.
OL,10,FEverything is available at hand. I
OL,11,Fjust love the town."
OL,13,FSo it's not all doom and gloom. But as
OL,14,Fbusinesses, councils, and shoppers
OL,15,Fknow all too well, the combination of
OL,16,Finvestment, and customer support -
OL,17,Fwhich appears to be helping businesses
OL,18,Fin Wigston - is hard to come by.
OL,26,@nD@TOUsD@TO]
